
REACT CSS
---------

        - Internal
        - External
        - Inline

    Here class properties  is called className

    Internal
    --------
        create one state object assign all style code key with value pair.

        const obj = {

            backgroundColor:'red'
            color :'blue'
            fontSize : '20px'

        }

        <div style = {obj} > React Tutorial </div>
    

    Inline.
    -------
        style attribute inside directly write css called inline.

        <div style = {{ backgroundColor:'red', color :'blue', fontSize : '20px' }} > React Tutorial </div>
    
    External 
    ---------
        - To create extnal css file add import your component.
        - css file inside write css code. no need follow key with value pair

        - exteal css file

                index.css (or) index.module.css

        - Community team is sugggest index.module.css it is avoiding overlapping.



BootStrap
---------
   step 1 :  npm install react-bootstrap bootstrap
   step 2 : add your index.js import 'bootstrap/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css';







